---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const waitlistUrl = '/hidden-profit-review/#waitlist';
---

<Base
  title="You're in. Here's the fast lane"
  description="Thanks for telling Jonathan what's next for your agent. The review waitlist is the fast lane to personal help on your workflow."
  noindex
>
  <div class="container next-page">
    <div class="book-hero panel">
      <p class="book-kicker">Got it &middot; One more step</p>
      <h1>Want me on your workflow personally?</h1>

      <p class="book-sub">
        You just told me where you want to take your agent. When I work a
        workflow personally, it runs through the Hidden Profit Review &mdash; and
        because I run every review myself, I take on a handful a month. The
        waitlist holds your place in line.
      </p>

      <div class="book-cta-wrap">
        <a href={waitlistUrl} class="book-cta" data-track="cta:waitlist-next">
          <span class="book-cta-main">Join the review waitlist &rarr;</span>
          <span class="book-cta-sub">30 seconds &middot; your spot holds, no obligation</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <ul class="book-benefits">
        <li>I read every entry personally, and invites go out in order</li>
        <li>A clear read on whether your workflow is worth automating, or an honest &ldquo;not yet&rdquo;</li>
        <li>No pitch, no slides, just your work and a plan</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="book-reassure">
        Not ready? Keep building &mdash; the <a href="/ai-assistant/">guides</a> stay free, and your survey answers already shape what I publish next.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
